## Description {#details}

A node in a MsgPack <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/msgpack/document">Document</a>.

This is a simple copyable and passable-by-value type that does not own any memory.

Definition at line 38 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/binaryformat/msgpackdocument-h">MsgPackDocument.h</a>.

## Public Operators

### operator=() {#add2f7af8865179511cd97536891b2a9b}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>DocNode &amp; llvm::msgpack::DocNode::operator= (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> char &#42; Val)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Convenience assignment operators.

This only works if the destination <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/msgpack/docnode">DocNode</a> has an associated <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/msgpack/document">Document</a>, i.e. it was not constructed using the default constructor. The string one does not copy, so the string must remain valid for the lifetime of the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/msgpack/document">Document</a>. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a> fromString to avoid that restriction.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/binaryformat/msgpackdocument-h/#l00207">207</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/binaryformat/msgpackdocument-h">MsgPackDocument.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### fromString() {#a0a2160ffa04d67291e2827a29994a3b9}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>StringRef DocNode::fromString (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> S, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Tag=&quot;&quot;)</>}>
Convert the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> and use it to set this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/msgpack/docnode">DocNode</a> (assuming scalar).

If it is a string, copy the string into the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/msgpack/document">Document</a>&#39;s strings list so we do not rely on S having a lifetime beyond this call. Tag is &quot;&quot; or a YAML tag.
